<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-15T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115/14100: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-15T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            15, 1918—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>786. It having become impracticable for Nielsen to proceed to London,
                                Department desires you to address a communication to Foreign Office
                                in sense of Department’s telegram No. 180, July 12, beginning with
                                words: “The Department has given careful consideration”.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>